<refnamediv><refname>imbwperim3</refname><refpurpose>Extract exposed surface voxels from a 3-D binary volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imbwperim3(volume)
out = imbwperim3(volume, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 3-D volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para><literal>6</literal>, <literal>18</literal>, or <literal>26</literal>. Default is 6.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean volume of foreground surface voxels.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Marks each foreground voxel that touches background or a volume boundary under the selected 3-D connectivity.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
volume = zeros(31, 31, 17) == 1;
volume(7:25, 7:25, 4:14) = %t;
surface = imbwperim3(volume, 6);
imshow3d(surface, "3d", 1, 8000);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
